    <td class="roweven" valign="top" width="2000">Improvement: As per a suggestion from Mathieu CLABAUT the feralotf# highlight groups now use the default keyword, This allows you to override these default colors easily.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
        <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap><a href="download_script.php?src_id=1965">otf.vim</a></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap><b>0.2</b></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap><i>2003-05-03</i></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" nowrap>6.0</td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top"><i><a href="/account/profile.php?user_id=818">Robert KellyIV</a></i></td>
    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" width="2000">Small update: converted :OTF1-8 into :OTF which takes a count (line number position) and takes optional bang to specify string as a keyword (think register)<br>Keywords are:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(w) cword,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; expand(&quot;&lt;cword&gt;&quot;)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(W) \&lt;cword\&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&quot;\\&lt;&quot;.expand(&quot;&lt;cword&gt;&quot;).&quot;\\&gt;&quot;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(&quot;) unnamed register&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; @@<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(/) current search string&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;@/<br>i.e. &quot;:2OTF! /&quot; (bang) will pull in the current search string and color it in color group2, while &quot;:2OTF /&quot; (no bang) will color '/' in color group2<br><br>Original :OTF1-8 commands updated to bang style but commented out (just in case anyone liked that method)</td>
</tr>
